The paper deals with secure source coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves information leakage and eavesdropping, which are related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of side information is a common theme throughout the paper, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) or signal processing (cs.SI) categories. Finally, the paper deals with coding and rate-distortion trade-offs, which are topics in communication theory (cs.CC).
